In [ ]:
colleges=[]
Type=[]
Establish=[]
city=[]
seats=[]
state=[]
fee=[]
for i in range(1,19):
    url=f"https://www.indiaccess.com/colleges/medical/index.asp?currentpage={i}"
    page=requests.get(url)
    soup=BeautifulSoup(page.content)
    a=soup.find_all("div",attrs={"class":"panel-body"})
    s=soup.find_all("li",attrs={"class":"list-group-item"})
    st=soup.find_all("div",attrs={"class":"additional-info"})
    fe=soup.find_all('li',attrs={"class":'list-group-item'})
    
    #for college name 
    for i in a:
        b=i.text
        colleges.append(b.split(",")[0].replace("\n",""))
        
        
    
    #for Type of college name
    for i in a:
        d=i.text
        Type.append(re.findall("([A-Za-z]+);",d)[0])
        
        
        
    #for Established Year    
    for i in a:
        d=i.text
        f=re.findall("\s(\d\d\d\d);",d)
        Establish.append(f[0])
    
    
    
    #for City of the college
    for i in a:
        c=i.text.split(",")[1]
        city.append(re.findall("\s[A-za-z\sA-za-z]+",c)[0].split("\n")[0].replace(" ",""))

    
    
    #for Seats of the college
    for i in s:
        a=i.text
        b=re.findall("Seats:(\s\d+)",a)
        if len(b)>0:
            seats.append(b[0])
    

    
    #for State of the college
    for i in st:
        state.append(i.text.split(",")[-1].replace(" ",""))
    
    

    
print(len(colleges))
print(len(Type))
print(len(Establish))
print(len(city))
print(len(state))

print(len(seats))
